===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|mīl}}, from a Germanic borrowing of {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|mīlia}}, {{m|la|mīllia}}, plural of {{m|la|mīle}}, {{m|la|mīlle||mile}} (literally ‘thousand’ but used as a short form of {{m|la|[[mīlle]] [[passūs]]||a thousand paces}}).  Cognate with Dutch {{term|mijl|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Meile|lang=de}}.

